titleInfo.title: USA v. Natoli et al
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER - A hearing on the government's motion is scheduled before the undersigned United States district judge on January 2, 2007, at 3:30 p.m. in Courtroom No. 3, Roman L. Hruska U.S.Courthouse, 111 South 18th Plaza, Omaha, Nebraska.Counsel for the defendant, if previously appointed pursuant to the Criminal Justice Act,is reappointed to represent the defendant for purposes of the Rule 35(b) motion. If retained, counsel for the defendant remains as counsel for the defendant until the Rule 35(b) motion isresolved or until given leave to withdraw.The Federal Public Defender shall provide CJA counsel with a new voucher.The Clerk of the Court shall electronically serve a copy of this order on counsel for the government, counsel for the defendant, and the Federal Public Defender.The Marshal is directed to keep the defendant in the district for this hearing.as to defendant(s) Rita J. Natoli. (cc to USM) Ordered by Judge Joseph F. Bataillon.(TJS)

titleInfo.title: USA v. Natoli et al
titleInfo.subTitle: AMENDED JUDGMENT (Reduction of Sentence) as to Rita J. Natoli, Defendant pleaded guilty to count I of the Indictment and is sentenced to Time Served. Defendant shall be on Supervised Release for a term of 5 years. While on Supervised Release the defendant shall be on electronic monitoring for a period of 90 consecutive days as one of the conditions of her Supervised Release; the $100.00 Special Assessment has been paid in full; Count 5 of the indictment is dismissed on the motion of the United States; the defendant is remanded to the custody of the United States Marshal to be release after processing as to defendant(s) Rita J. Natoli Ordered by Judge Joseph F. Bataillon.(PCV, ) (4 cc to US Marshal)
